      "side": 1,
      "message": "Consider restructuring this whole code as:\n\ntype visitor func(buck *v1.Verifiers_TryJobVerifier_Bucket, b *v1.BuilderProto)\n\nfunc visitBuilders(ctx *validation.Context, tryCfg *v1.Verifiers_TryJobVerifier, cb visitor) {\n  for _, buck :\u003d range tryCfg.Buckets {\n    ctx.Enter(\"bucket %s:\", buck.Name)\n    for _, b :\u003d range buck.Builders {\n      ctx.Enter(\"builder %s:\", b.Name)\n      cb(buck, b)\n      ctx.Exit()\n    }\n    ctx.Exit()\n  }\n}\n\nAnd then make two passes using this visitor: one to collect all the various maps, and another to do the actual validation. I think it will somewhat reduce nesting and clutter.\n\n(Also I gave up reviewing this CL from scratch at this point, will review only the diff).",
